                            <comment id="14156656" author="carlyeks" created="Thu, 2 Oct 2014 15:15:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;We can just use the metadata that we already have if it is not a secondary index instead of looking it up in the schema. Otherwise, LGTM.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14156682" author="tjake" created="Thu, 2 Oct 2014 15:52:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;That metadata is from the sstable which is why we need the live metadata connected to get the latest crc_check_chance (see &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-7978&quot; title=&quot;CrcCheckChance should not be stored as part of an sstable&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-7978&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-7978&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
